img.com/photo/msid-132018534,imgsize-1281419.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian woman dies in Canada in apartment fire, could never visit her parents since she left in 2020]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132017855.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A devastating fire in Bridgewater, Nova Scotia, claimed the life of 24-year-old Amitoj Kaur, an international student from India. Kaur, who supported her ailing father and family back home, was the sole fatality in the blaze that engulfed a residential building. Her uncle has launched a fundraiser to repatriate her body to India for final rites, highlighting the immense financial strain on her grieving family.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indian-woman-dies-in-canada-after-fire-catches-her-apartment-could-never-visit-her-parents-since-she-left-in-2020/articleshow/132017855.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/indian-woman-dies-in-canada-after-fire-catches-her-apartment-could-never-visit-her-parents-since-she-left-in-2020/articleshow/132017855.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T19:32:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132017887,imgsize-62514.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Storm discovery: Grave hidden for more than 100 years uncovered after New York storm topples giant tree]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132017802.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/storm-discovery-grave-hidden-for-more-than-100-years-uncovered-after-new-york-storm-topples-giant-tree/articleshow/132017802.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/storm-discovery-grave-hidden-for-more-than-100-years-uncovered-after-new-york-storm-topples-giant-tree/articleshow/132017802.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T19:34:34+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132017948,imgsize-1966997.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Europe on red alert as record heatwave pushes health systems to brink]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132017678.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Scientists described the spell of extreme weather, which began on June 20, as the most severe heatwave ever recorded in Europe. They warned that the continent, which is warming faster than any other region on Earth, is facing increasingly frequent and intense heat extremes driven by climate change. France and Britain remained among the worst-affected countries, with both experiencing record-breaking June temperatures.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/europe-on-red-alert-as-record-heatwave-pushes-health-systems-to-brink/articleshow/132017678.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/europe-on-red-alert-as-record-heatwave-pushes-health-systems-to-brink/articleshow/132017678.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T19:26:20+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132017765,imgsize-230423.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Because you sent LinkedIn request to USCIS staff: Is this a new ground to deny naturalization?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132016269.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A US citizenship applicant was denied naturalization after sending a LinkedIn request to USCIS officials. USCIS stated this action raised concerns about potentially threatening or improperly influential behavior, equating it to threats their personnel face. An attorney commented that it was an unusual case as there is no accusation of any actual contact but just a social media invitaion.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/because-you-sent-a-linkedin-follow-request-to-a-uscis-staff-is-this-a-new-ground-on-which-us-can-deny-naturalization/articleshow/132016269.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/because-you-sent-a-linkedin-follow-request-to-a-uscis-staff-is-this-a-new-ground-on-which-us-can-deny-naturalization/articleshow/132016269.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T18:01:31+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132016333,imgsize-50812.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[16 men, including Indian-origin accused arrested in Canada after extortion probe]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132002979.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a significant crackdown, Calgary police charged 16 men, primarily of Indian descent on visas, linked to a widespread extortion scheme targeting the South Asian community. While mugshots of 15 suspects have been publicly released, only one remains detained, with the others granted bail. Investigators are examining possible connections to the Bishnoi gang in light of 49 reported extortion cases, including several shootings, since April 2025.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/16-men-including-indian-origin-accused-arrested-in-canada-after-south-asian-extortion-probe-all-released-on-bail-except-one/articleshow/132002979.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/16-men-including-indian-origin-accused-arrested-in-canada-after-south-asian-extortion-probe-all-released-on-bail-except-one/articleshow/132002979.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T18:06:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132015686,imgsize-105126.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Dubai ruler Sheikh Hamdan approves three major Dubai projects including AI park, 8km Creek upgrade and Falcon market]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132015259.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Dubai is launching ambitious new projects blending AI, heritage, and urban design to enhance living, working, and visiting experiences.  Key initiatives include the world's first AI-designed park, a dedicated Falcon Market celebrating Emirati culture, and an 8km lighting transformation of Dubai Creek. These developments aim to boost quality of life, preserve identity, and attract tourism, aligning with the Dubai 2040 Urban Master Plan.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/dubai-ruler-sheikh-hamdan-approves-three-major-dubai-projects-including-ai-park-8km-creek-upgrade-and-falcon-market/articleshow/132015259.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/dubai-ruler-sheikh-hamdan-approves-three-major-dubai-projects-including-ai-park-8km-creek-upgrade-and-falcon-market/articleshow/132015259.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T17:27:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132015391,imgsize-485938.cms"/></item><item><title><!